{"key":"post-9734500","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9734500</id>\n<content>Oysters will grow on pf tek, but in truth it's just a novelty grow to learn the basics.&amp;nbsp; You can't grow enough to be worth the time and money as food.&amp;nbsp; However, you can spawn the fully colonized brf cakes to sawdust and woodchips, which is what I'd recommend to do with at least half your first batch of cakes.&amp;nbsp; They also grow well on shredded paper, so you can score ecology points at school by recycling old tests and other paper waste from the various classes into mushrooms.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Oysters require far more FAE than cubes, so if you use a shotgun terrarium, leave the lid off and mist more to make up for lost moisture.&amp;nbsp; Keep them in a cool place, because oysters get thin and paper-like at room temperature.&amp;nbsp; At 50F, they'll form nice meaty fruits that will knock your socks off in a stir fry.&amp;nbsp; I've found that the unheated crawl space under my house is perfect for oysters in the winter.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9734554</next>\n<prev>9734480</prev>\n<first>9734480</first>\n<last>9734647</last>\n<when>1233779357</when>\n<utime>02/04/09 10:29 PM</utime>\n</post>"}